      • isIsElementary

        boolean isIsElementary()
        Getter for attribute 'GeneralClass.IsElementary' Metamodel description: Determines whether a Class is elementary/primitive or not. A Class is primitive if its value cannot be broken down and its instances are not handled by the application. For example, integer and boolean are elementary Classes, whereas Human or Device are generally not.
